I had them both running early in the summer but elected to use another outboard for my other boat they were on. The Thompson is in good shape and needs a little work to be water ready. The bilge was painted with the modern equivalent of "red lead" to discourage any rot/fungus in that area. The floors are temporarily installed along with the seats. These panels are just leaning against the side in the pics to give an idea how they go/look. Not pictured are various teak trim pieces that go on the gunwales. They were removed at one point for refinishing and are in excellent condition. There is also a near perfect replacement windshield frame that only needs a little finishing work. The windshield on the boat already is original and in pretty good shape. The replacement was on another Thompson I had that got scrapped. The motor on the boat was hung there and never rigged.
